        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 11.  OF THE SALE WITH A RIGHT OF REDEMPTION
Art. 2567.  Right of redemption, definition
The parties to a contract of sale may agree that the seller shall have the right of redemption, which is the right to take back the thing from the buyer.</p>
        </content>
